On Fri, 29 Oct 1999, Michael Cummins wrote:
> 	Just wondering if you know something about ide-scsi.
> Should you turn off all UDMA or DMA on the drives which are using this
> emulating module??
If they are CDROMs on VIA chipset, then yes. You should disable DMA on
these drives with hdparm.
